{"ast":null,"code":"import _objectSpread from \"/home/tecot/development/dsm/dsm-client/node_modules/@babel/runtime/helpers/esm/objectSpread2.js\";\nimport { mapActions } from 'vuex';\nexport default {\n  data: function data() {\n    return {\n      cookieDivOr: false,\n      privacyPolicyShow: false\n    };\n  },\n  mounted: function mounted() {\n    if (!this.$store.state.showPrivacyPolicy) {\n      this.cookieDivOr = true;\n      this.setIfShowedPrivacyPolicy(true);\n    }\n  },\n  methods: _objectSpread(_objectSpread({}, mapActions(['setIfShowedPrivacyPolicy'])), {}, {\n    closeDiv: function closeDiv() {\n      this.cookieDivOr = false;\n    },\n    viewPrivacyPolicy: function viewPrivacyPolicy() {\n      this.privacyPolicyShow = true;\n    }\n  })\n};","map":{"version":3,"names":["mapActions","data","cookieDivOr","privacyPolicyShow","mounted","$store","state","showPrivacyPolicy","setIfShowedPrivacyPolicy","methods","_objectSpread","closeDiv","viewPrivacyPolicy"],"sources":["src/components/shared/PrivacyPolicy.vue"],"sourcesContent":["<!--\n * @File name: \n * @Author: Tecot (tyx_cqbs@163.com)\n * @Version: V1.0\n * @Date: 2024-12-16 11:27:03\n * @Description: \n-->\n<template>\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <div class=\"cookieDiv\" v-if=\"cookieDivOr\">\n      <span style=\"text-align: center\" >We would like to use cookies to better understand your usage of this website. \n        This will help improve your experience when visiting this website in the future. \n        Regarding the use of cookies and how to revoke or manage your consent, \n        please refer to our <a href=\"##\" @click=\"viewPrivacyPolicy\">Privacy Policy</a>. \n        If you click the confirm button on the right, \n        it will be deemed that you agree to the use of cookies.\n      </span>\n      <div class=\"aDiv\">\n        <a href=\"##\" style=\"margin-left:2.16em;\" @click=\"closeDiv\">I agree</a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <el-dialog\n      :visible.sync=\"privacyPolicyShow\"\n      title=\"Privacy policy\"\n      width=\"30%\">\n      <div class=\"content\">\n        <p>This software is well aware of the importance of user information to users, and will do its utmost to protect the personal information security of users to maintain your trust and support for us. We hope to explain to you through this \"Privacy Policy\" how we collect, use, store, and share this information when you use our services, as well as the ways we provide for you to access, update, control, and protect this information.\nThis \"Privacy Policy\" is closely related to the services you use with this software. We hope you will read it carefully so that you can make appropriate choices according to the guidelines of this policy when needed. Before using the various services of this software, please be sure to read and thoroughly understand this policy and make a choice that you think is suitable for the current situation. Once you start using the various services of this software, it means that you have fully understood and agreed to this policy, and it also means that you agree to us collecting, using, storing, and sharing your related information according to this \"Privacy Policy\".\nThis policy will help you understand the following content:</p>\n<br>\n<p>1. How we collect and use your personal information</p>\n<p>2. How we use Cookies and similar technologies</p>\n<p>3. How we share, transfer, and publicly disclose your personal information</p>\n<p>4. How we protect your personal information</p>\n<p>5. Your rights</p>\n<p>6. About children's personal information</p>\n<p>7. How your personal information is transferred globally</p>\n<p>8. How this policy is updated</p>\n\nI. The information we may collect\n\nWhen we provide services, we may collect, store, and use the following information related to you. If you do not provide relevant information, you may not be able to register as our user or enjoy some of the services we offer, or the services may not achieve the desired effect.\n\n1. Information you provide:\n\n   - The personal information you provide when you register for an account or use our services, such as phone numbers, email addresses, or bank card numbers;\n\n   - The shared information you provide to others through our services, as well as the information you store when using our services.\n\n2. Information shared by others about you\n\n   - Shared information about you provided by others when they use our services.\n\n3. Information we obtain about you\n\nII. The information we may collect when you use our services:\n\n1. Log information, referring to the technical information that may be automatically collected by the system through cookies, web beacons, or other methods when you use our services, including:\n\n2. Device or software information, such as configuration information provided by your mobile device, web browser, or other programs used to access our services, your IP address, and the version and device identifier used by your mobile device;\n\n3. Information about your search or browsing when using our services, such as the web search terms you use, the URL addresses of social media pages you visit, and other information and content details you browse or request when using our services;\n\n4. Information about the mobile applications (APPs) and other software you have used, as well as information about your use of such mobile applications and software;\n\n5. Information about your communications through our services, such as the accounts you have communicated with, as well as the time, data, and duration of the communications;\n\n6. Information contained in the content you share through our services (metadata), such as the date, time, or location of the shared photos or videos you shoot or upload.\n\n7. Location information, referring to information about your location collected when you enable device location services and use our location-based services, including:\n\n8. Your geographical location information collected through GPS or WiFi when you use our services with location-enabled mobile devices;\n\n9. Real-time information about your geographical location provided by you or others, such as the region information you provide in your account information, shared information showing your current or past geographical location, and geo-tagged information in photos shared by you or others;\n\n10. You can stop the collection of your geographical location information by turning off the location feature.\n\nIII. How we may collect information\n\n1. We or our third-party partners may collect and use your information through cookies and web beacons and store such information as log information.\n\n2. We use our own cookies and web beacons to provide you with a more personalized user experience and services, and for the following purposes:\n\n   - Remembering your identity. For example, cookies and web beacons help us recognize you as a registered user of ours or save preferences or other information you provide to us;\n\n   - Analyzing your use of our services. For example, we can use cookies and web beacons to understand what activities you engage in when using our services or which pages or services are most popular with you;\n\n   - Advertising optimization. Cookies and web beacons help us provide you with relevant advertisements instead of general advertising.\n\n3. While we use cookies and web beacons for the above purposes, we may also provide advertisers or other partners with non-personally identifiable information collected through cookies and web beacons, which has been statistically processed, for analyzing how users use our services and for advertising services.\n\n4. Our products and services may have cookies and web beacons placed by advertisers or other partners. These cookies and web beacons may collect non-personally identifiable information related to you to analyze how users use the services, send you advertisements that may interest you, or assess the effectiveness of advertising services. These third-party cookies and web beacons collect and use such information, which is not subject to this \"Privacy Policy\" but is subject to the privacy policies of the relevant users. We are not responsible for third-party cookies or web beacons.\n\n5. You can refuse or manage cookies or web beacons through browser settings. However, please note that if you disable cookies or web beacons, you may not enjoy the best service experience, and some services may not function properly. At the same time, you will still receive the same amount of advertising, but the relevance of the advertisements to you will be reduced.\n\nIV. How we may use information\n\n1. We may use the information collected in the process of providing services for the following purposes:\n\n   - To provide you with our services;\n\n   - For identity verification, customer service, security prevention, fraud detection, archiving, and backup purposes when providing our services, ensuring the security of the products and services we provide to you;\n\n   - To help us design new services and improve our existing services;\n\n   - To help us better understand how you access and use our services to respond to your personalized needs, such as language settings, location settings, personalized help services, and instructions, or to respond to you and other users in other ways;\n\n   - To provide you with more relevant advertisements instead of general advertising;\n\n   - To evaluate the effectiveness of advertisements and other promotional and promotional activities in our services and improve them;\n\n   - Software certification or management of software upgrades;\n\n   - To allow you to participate in surveys related to our products and services.\n\n2. To give you a better experience, improve our services, or for other purposes you agree to, in accordance with relevant laws and regulations, we may use the information collected through a particular service in an aggregated or personalized manner for our other services. For example, information collected when you use one of our services may be used in another service to provide you with specific content or display information that is relevant to you, rather than universally pushed. If we provide corresponding options in the relevant services, you can also authorize us to use the information provided and stored by that service for our other services.\n\nV. How you can access and control personal information\n\nWe will do everything possible to take appropriate technical measures to ensure that you can access, update, and correct your registration information or other personal information provided when using our services. When accessing, updating, correcting, and deleting the aforementioned information, we may require you to verify your identity to ensure account security.\n\nVI. The information we may share\n\nExcept in the following circumstances, without your consent, we and our affiliated companies will not share your personal information with any third party:\n\n1. We and our affiliated companies may share your personal information with our affiliated companies, partners, and third-party service providers, contractors, and agents (such as communication service providers who send emails or push notifications on our behalf, map service providers who provide location data for us) for the following purposes:\n\n   - To provide you with our services;\n\n   - To achieve the purposes stated in the \"How We May Use Information\" section;\n\n   - To fulfill our obligations under this \"Privacy Policy\" and exercise our rights;\n\n   - To understand, maintain, and improve our services.\n\n2. If we or our affiliated companies share your personal information with any of the above third parties, we will strive to ensure that they comply with this \"Privacy Policy\" and other appropriate confidentiality and security measures we require when using your personal information.\n\n3. As our business continues to develop, we and our affiliated companies may undergo mergers, acquisitions, asset transfers, or similar transactions, and your personal information may be transferred as part of such transactions. We will notify you before the transfer.\n\n4. We or our affiliated companies may also retain, preserve, or disclose your personal information for the following needs:\n\n   - To comply with applicable laws and regulations;\n\n   - To comply with court orders or other legal procedures;\n\n   - To comply with requests from relevant government agencies;\n\n   - For purposes reasonably necessary to comply with applicable laws, maintain public interest, or protect the personal and property safety or legitimate rights and interests of our customers, us, our group companies, other users, or employees.\n\nVII. Information Security\n\nWe retain your personal information only for the period necessary for the purposes stated in this \"Privacy Policy\" and the time limits required by laws and regulations. For children's personal information,\n\n      </div>\n      <span slot=\"footer\" class=\"dialog-footer\">\n        <el-button type=\"primary\" @click=\"privacyPolicyShow = false\">Confirm</el-button>\n      </span>\n    </el-dialog>\n  </div>\n  \n</template>\n\n<script>\nimport { mapActions } from 'vuex'\nexport default {\n  data() {\n    return {\n      cookieDivOr: false,\n      privacyPolicyShow: false\n    }\n  },\n  mounted() {\n    \n    if(!this.$store.state.showPrivacyPolicy) {\n      this.cookieDivOr = true\n      this.setIfShowedPrivacyPolicy(true)\n    }\n  },\n  methods: {\n    ...mapActions([\n      'setIfShowedPrivacyPolicy'\n    ]),\n    closeDiv() {\n      this.cookieDivOr = false\n    },\n    viewPrivacyPolicy() {\n      this.privacyPolicyShow = true\n    }\n  }\n}\n</script>\n\n<style lang=\"scss\" scoped>\n.cookieDiv {\n  width: 100%;\n  background: #324277;\n  height: 60px;\n  position: fixed;\n  bottom:0px;\n  z-index: 1000;\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: space-between;\n  margin:0 auto;\n}\n.cookieDiv span {\n  color: #f0f3fb;\n  font-size: 16px;\n  margin-left:20px;\n}\n.cookieDiv a {\n  color: #008B8B;\n}\n.cookieDiv .aDiv a {\n  height: 60px;\n  width:100px;\n  background: #008B8B;\n  color: white;\n  font-size: 18px;\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: center;\n  text-decoration: none;\n}\n.content {\n  height: 400px;\n  overflow-y: scroll;\n}\n</style>"],"mappings":";AAmKA,SAAAA,UAAA;AACA;EACAC,IAAA,WAAAA,KAAA;IACA;MACAC,WAAA;MACAC,iBAAA;IACA;EACA;EACAC,OAAA,WAAAA,QAAA;IAEA,UAAAC,MAAA,CAAAC,KAAA,CAAAC,iBAAA;MACA,KAAAL,WAAA;MACA,KAAAM,wBAAA;IACA;EACA;EACAC,OAAA,EAAAC,aAAA,CAAAA,aAAA,KACAV,UAAA,EACA,2BACA;IACAW,QAAA,WAAAA,SAAA;MACA,KAAAT,WAAA;IACA;IACAU,iBAAA,WAAAA,kBAAA;MACA,KAAAT,iBAAA;IACA;EAAA;AAEA","ignoreList":[]},"metadata":{},"sourceType":"module","externalDependencies":[]}